  "text": "Comparing results for four groups of participants ages 4 to 6, 7 to 9, 10 to 12, and 15 to 16 [CITATION_1] , the items included in the image of Jewish men increased by age with all pairwise comparisons between age groups reaching signifi cance. However, the items included in the image of Arab men increased signifi cantly across age groups only until the ages of 10 to 12, and for this and the following age-group (13 to 15) the complexity of the image of the Jew exceeded signifi cantly that of the Arab (Figure 18.2a ) .",
